title: Nissan's prototype Leaf tests new autonomous technology - Automotive News
text:
Requested Article Nissan's prototype Leaf tests new autonomous technology 
Nissan, aiming to put autonomous vehicles on the road by 2020, has unveiled its latest prototype, a sensor-laden Leaf electric vehicle that can change lanes, pass cars and merge onto and off of highway by itself. The system previews a new technology called Piloted Drive 1.0 that Nissan says it will offer in Japan by the end of next year. You must be a subscriber to Automotive News to continue reading.
